    <note>Cai(1) Yu(4) [21364] The Cai(1) of Danyang considered him their wise and virtuous ancestor. Therefore, all Danyang Cai(1) must be lineal descendants. In order to reconcile this with chronological logic, he would be the grandfather of Yuan(3) [21365], whose biography establishes the fact that the family was a wealthy one, and Qiu, whose great grandson's funerary inscription describes Yuan(3)'s son, Zhao [1648] as a granduncle. This means that Yu(4) probable earned the jinshi at a relatively advanced age, not unlikely for the first one in the family. See documentation for Cai(1) Dachun. Zhishun Zhenjiang zhi, 18.5a. CBD, 5, 3795.[Not yet checked. 未考。]</note>
